{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SAN DIEGO JAIL - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the intake area of a busy San Diego precinct, Helena sits on a bench and regroups.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Detectives move past her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Handcuffed criminals are separated, bagged and tagged.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: beautifully dressed man, ARNIE METZGER, 30's, super- lawyer, knows everyone from the top of the system to the bottom, slick but likable, smart and ruthless, too, separates himself from a DETECTIVE he's gladhanding and approaches Helena.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE
{DIALOGUE}: Helena, I'm so sorry --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: Arnie, thank God.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Metzger sits, giving her a hug.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: Can you please tell me what on earth is going on?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arnie looks at her as if to say, "do you really not know?"
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then, he speaks quietly with his hand in front of his mouth.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE
{DIALOGUE}: I understand.
{DIALOGUE}: You're upset.
{DIALOGUE}: You want to know what's going on.
{DIALOGUE}: That's good.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: Why are you talking like that?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE
{DIALOGUE}: Listen to me carefully.
{DIALOGUE}: First of all, Carl isn't here.
{DIALOGUE}: DEA's got him and they'll hang on to him until arraignment, which will probably be tomorrow.
{DIALOGUE}: So here you're wasting your time.
{DIALOGUE}: Are you with me?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He checks to see if this is registering.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE
{DIALOGUE}: Good.
{DIALOGUE}: From now on I want you to expect that every word you utter will be tape-recorded, that the movement of your lips is being read.
{DIALOGUE}: Got it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: Arnie, this is crazy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He makes eye contact with her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE
{DIALOGUE}: Got it?
{META_DATA}: (she slowly nods)
{DIALOGUE}: Good.
{DIALOGUE}: Do not discuss anything over the telephone.
{DIALOGUE}: Do not talk to the neighbors.
{DIALOGUE}: Stay out of your yard.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: What is he being charged with?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know, but under no circumstances would I talk about it here.
{DIALOGUE}: I want you to go home and relax the best you can.
{DIALOGUE}: Continue your life as if nothing has happened.
{DIALOGUE}: That is very important.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: Arnie, I feel like Alice stepping through the looking glass.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE
{DIALOGUE}: That's a very apt analogy, Helena.
{DIALOGUE}: Now, go home and be with your children.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BUILDING PARKING LOT - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena exits.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her expression is set as she drives.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns a corner in the shopping district, passing JAVIER AND MANOLO who are walking down the street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tourists, drunk Marines and the homeless piss away another day.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We follow them into a bar with blackened windows and a discrete sign.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BAR - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This is a place where men come to meet men.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And it's already lively even at this early hour.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javier and Manolo find a seat and wait.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LATER
{DIALOGUE}: Javi is working on his second beer when he seems to recognize somebody.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ACROSS THE ROOM
