{CHARACTER_NAME}: SALAZAR
{META_DATA}: (clearly pleased with Javi)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm curious how you did this with such economy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{DIALOGUE}: Everybody has a weakness.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SOMEBODY'S PARENTS' MANSION, CINCINNATI - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With its old-growth trees and manipulated shrubbery, the large house is shrouded in the mystery of well-heeled suburbia.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is very late.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SOMEBODY'S PARENTS' MANSION - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Somebody's parents are out of town and the house feels empty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Big empty rooms with expensive furniture nobody sits on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Faint MUSIC echoes through the house.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. KITCHEN - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: High ceilings of a 1930's kitchen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vodka bottles and cranberry juice and limes are spilled across a counter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON THE RHODES AGAIN by Morcheeba plays from a jam-box on a counter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Maybe ten TEENAGERS are partying hard in this kitchen.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's weird and disassociated, people wandering in and out, playing with kitchen utensils, heavily fucked up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There are drugs on a mirror on the eat-in table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caroline and Seth and two friends sit around this table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: VANESSA, 16, almost pretty, is hitting a freebase pipe and holds the hit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FUCKED-UP BOWMAN, 17, super-preppy with a wan, Baby Huey face, takes a slug of vodka.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are jittery, sweaty, tweaked, fucked-up --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{DIALOGUE}: All I'm saying, what I'm saying, is it never seems like anybody ever says anything that matters to them, like we all look at each other and nod with responses we've been trained to make, not real responses, just social conventions, phony, fake smiles, surface bullshit... I mean, we're all smart and do we have any idea what each other are like, really like?
{DIALOGUE}: Do I know what Seth's afraid of, or Vanessa, or fucked-up Bowman?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Everyone looks at Fucked-up Bowman who grinds his jaw appreciatively --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{DIALOGUE}: ...Probably, but do I ever say this stuff, just say, "hey, I'm uncomfortable in this crowd, I don't know what the fuck I'm doing, either?
{DIALOGUE}: I know you're afraid and it's okay-- "
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Seth's words come quickly, they're riffing, totally in sync, totally wired --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SETH
{DIALOGUE}: We act like we have all the answers and we're totally invincible like our parents seem and their parents before them and it's fucking bullshit --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fucked-up Bowman takes another slug of vodka and almost pukes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FUCKED-UP BOWMAN
{DIALOGUE}: For instance --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SETH
{DIALOGUE}: For instance I know you jack-off thinking about Caroline even though you're supposedly "in love" with Vanessa.
{DIALOGUE}: Whatever the fuck that means?
{META_DATA}: (a digression)
{DIALOGUE}: I mean, what is that convention, anyway?
{DIALOGUE}: We're all these random collections of self-interest, and then we just decide that now we're two people walking along --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caroline expels a hit of rock cocaine --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{DIALOGUE}: And Vanessa doesn't think she's pretty so she does all these weird fucking diets which is totally about self- esteem.
{DIALOGUE}: And she's beautiful.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: And that's not even fair.
{DIALOGUE}: Because listen to me.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm fucking lying right now.
{DIALOGUE}: This is exactly what I'm talking about... I'm supposedly talking about you, making some big point about you, and it's really about me.
{DIALOGUE}: So I should talk about me, not you, not even the universal "you..."
{META_DATA}: (takes a beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Okay.
{DIALOGUE}: Okay, I'm worried I'm not really smart or that I'm not nearly as smart as people think I am, or that my parents' expectations have been way too high since I was five, I mean who knows they're going to Harvard when they're five, not that I'm blaming them for anything because everything's great, and I may not even get in, but we all feel this shit and we never acknowledge it and if we can't acknowledge it to the people we care the most about then who will we ever say it too and what kind of life will that be?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They all look at each other with love.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This is an adventure and they're having a connection --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FUCKED-UP BOWMAN
{DIALOGUE}: I jack-off thinking about Seth.
{DIALOGUE}: Everybody I know does.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bowman does another huge hit of freebase.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{META_DATA}: (disgusted)
{DIALOGUE}: Ach, that's what I'm talking about.
{DIALOGUE}: Sarcasm.
{DIALOGUE}: Always fucking sarcasm.
{DIALOGUE}: You're afraid and you think if you admit it people will think you're weak or won't like you --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SETH
{DIALOGUE}: We live our lives by these unspoken rules that are handed to us.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They all look at each other, vibrating with the moment --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VANESSA
{DIALOGUE}: Let's be different --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FUCKED-UP BOWMAN
{DIALOGUE}: I can't feel my hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bowman looks around, squinting, confused.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's chalk white.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FUCKED-UP BOWMAN
{DIALOGUE}: I'm serious --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly, he clutches his chest and begins to twitch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Puke and foam come from his mouth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He seizes and falls from the chair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vanessa SCREAMS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Seth and Caroline push the table aside to get a better look.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Other people in the kitchen slowly take notice.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VANESSA
{DIALOGUE}: He's blue.
{DIALOGUE}: He isn't breathing --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{DIALOGUE}: Is he breathing?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bowman's eyes have rolled back in his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SETH
{DIALOGUE}: What do we do?
{DIALOGUE}: Okay.
{DIALOGUE}: Fucked-up Bowman's turning blue.
{DIALOGUE}: Doctor.
{DIALOGUE}: We need a doctor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VANESSA
{DIALOGUE}: Your dad's a doctor.
{DIALOGUE}: Call him --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SETH
{DIALOGUE}: He's a research doctor.
{DIALOGUE}: You're dad's a doctor, too --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VANESSA
{DIALOGUE}: What kind of research?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SETH
{DIALOGUE}: Mapping the fucking pig genome.
{DIALOGUE}: We'll call your dad, he's a neurosurgeon --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VANESSA
