{DIALOGUE}: As a parent.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARBARA
{DIALOGUE}: She asked me not to.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He leaves the room.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. UPSTAIRS HALLWAY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert is in the hallway, at Caroline's door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He opens it and we get BLASTED WITH MUSIC.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caroline is sitting in a rocking chair with headphones on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She faces the window and moves back and forth, back and forth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert calls her name, but the SOUNDTRACK is drowning him out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He calls again, this time apparently loud enough for her to hear.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She takes the headphones off - the MUSIC stops - and turns to look at him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Or rather, she looks right through him, as though he didn't exist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert is so taken aback by the coldness of her gaze that he doesn't speak.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns away from him and puts the headphones back on.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. MILITARY BASE - MEXICO - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javier and Salazar walk across the base.
