{CHARACTER_NAME}: SALAZAR
{DIALOGUE}: When he loves me like a father, he will never tell anyone he was here.
{DIALOGUE}: He will freely give the names of his superiors.
{DIALOGUE}: Then we get them and they too will give us names.
{DIALOGUE}: And eventually somebody will get us to Juan Obregon and the cartel will fall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They enter the barracks.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CELL - MEXICAN MILITARY BASE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's pitch black in the cell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's a human in here, but we can't see him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly the door is thrown open and light floods in, illuminating a very broken Francisco Flores.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The figure of Commander Salazar fills the doorway.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SALAZAR
{DIALOGUE}: This is shameful.
{DIALOGUE}: A disgrace.
{DIALOGUE}: Francisco Flores --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Francisco cowers in the corners --
