{DIALOGUE}: I have a drink before dinner to take the edge off my day.
{DIALOGUE}: That's different.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARBARA
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, it is?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, because the alternative is to be bored to death.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. WAKEFIELD HOUSE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He car pulls into the driveway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert gets out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barbara doesn't.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks back at her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARBARA
{DIALOGUE}: Why don't you go in and tell your daughter how bored you are.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She puts the car in reverse and drives away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stands for a moment, steaming.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. WAKEFIELD HOUSE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert Wakefield steps inside his home.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's very QUIET.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He checks the mail on the hall table.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. UPSTAIRS HALLWAY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert walks down the hallway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He steps into Caroline's bedroom.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CAROLINE WAKEFIELD'S BEDROOM - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert stands outside her closed bathroom door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is nothing, then from the other side of the door, the faint sound of a lighter CLICKING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AGAIN and AGAIN, then a COUGH.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CAROLINE WAKEFIELD'S BATHROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caroline sits on the toilet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Glamour Magazine on her lap.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's wild-eyed and paranoid.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The exhaust fan is running.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The aluminum foil is on the sink.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The last little bit of heroin in a wax-paper bundle sits beside it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's listening hard for any SOUND in the house.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: What she's wondering is if someone is outside the door listening.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She puts a piece of crack on the foil and listens hard once more before lighting it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She does the hit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And seems to feel better.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly there's a POUNDING on the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The VOICE of her father muffled through the solid wood.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT (V.O.)
{META_DATA}: (muffled by the door)
{DIALOGUE}: Caroline.
{DIALOGUE}: Open this door immediately.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caroline is up like a shot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The POUNDING on the door gets stronger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She crumples the foil and drops it in the toilet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bathroom door SOUNDS like it's about to cave inward.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{META_DATA}: (faking the best she can)
{DIALOGUE}: Who is it?
{DIALOGUE}: I'm going to the bathroom.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's coping now, full parallel process mode: she dumps the last heroin on the back of her hand and snorts it, checking her nose in the mirror as she reaches for a can of air freshener which she sprays into the air.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{DIALOGUE}: One minute.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She takes the remaining crack, lighters, tubes, little smudgy druggy bits of paraphernalia and carefully places it all in a hiding place above the bathroom cabinet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She pauses a beat, then opens the door, and tries to brush by her father while avoiding his eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{DIALOGUE}: Excuse me --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert grabs her by the arms.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pushes her against the wall and looks at her pupils.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks at her fingernails.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The blister on her thumb from working the lighter is red and irritated.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: You're not going anywhere, young lady.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She stands there; she's very high.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert sniffs the air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He throws open cabinets, searching for drugs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sees the smudge mark on the counter left by the charred aluminum foil.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: Where is it?
{DIALOGUE}: Where are the drugs?
{META_DATA}: (yelling)
{DIALOGUE}: Where are they?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{DIALOGUE}: Fuck you.
{DIALOGUE}: I wasn't doing anything.
{DIALOGUE}: You're like the Gestapo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert KICKS the cabinets.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: Fuck me?
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, okay.
{DIALOGUE}: Fuck me.
{DIALOGUE}: Fuck you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert is losing it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He throws stuff around the bathroom and then, for the first time, looks up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sees the long light in the box atop the medicine cabinet and it dawns on him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: I'm going to ask you one time to tell me the truth so that I can help you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She just stares.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: Okay, young lady, that's it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{DIALOGUE}: Like I give a fuck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert reaches above the medicine cabinet and pulls out a charred spoon.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It confuses him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He throws it into the sink.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls out another spoon.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls out crumpled bindles, rolled up, encrusted dollar bills, exhausted lighters, a pill bottle, an empty pint of vodka.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The detritus of drug addiction keeps on coming, filling up the sink.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert stares at it, the amount and complexity has him momentarily baffled.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: What is wrong with you?
{DIALOGUE}: What?
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: You're going away.
{DIALOGUE}: You're getting help somewhere.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{DIALOGUE}: You can't make me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, yes I can.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMITTED
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMITTED
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMITTED
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. - SAN DIEGO - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javier drinks toward downtown.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's sipping a Burger King soft-drink.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the seat next to him is a shopping bag from Target.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He takes an exit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javier pulls into the underground parking lot of a fancy office tower.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. POLICE SEDAN - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javi drives down to the third floor underground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls into a parking spot next to a white sedan.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slides open the cargo door of his van.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The cargo door of the sedan opens.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javi quickly gets into the sedan.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SEDAN - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Special Agents Hughes and Johnson welcome Javi.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{DIALOGUE}: Where are we going?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hughes sticks out his hand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HUGHES
{DIALOGUE}: Special Agent Hughes, Drug Enforcement Administration of the United States.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{META_DATA}: (ignoring the niceties)
{DIALOGUE}: Where are you taking me?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The agents exchange a look.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHNSON
{DIALOGUE}: Somewhere safe.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{DIALOGUE}: Where?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHNSON
