{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HUGHES
{DIALOGUE}: It's really safe.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{DIALOGUE}: Not for me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHNSON
{DIALOGUE}: Okay.
{DIALOGUE}: Where would you like to go?
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SWIMMING POOL - HOTEL - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javi and Agents Johnson and Hughes stand in the middle of the shallow end of a large swimming pool.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: KIDS in waterwings splash nearby.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{DIALOGUE}: It's important that we work together.
{DIALOGUE}: Mexico.
{DIALOGUE}: America.
{DIALOGUE}: One hand washing the other.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHNSON
{DIALOGUE}: We agree.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{DIALOGUE}: So... maybe you tell me about your informants in our operations.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHNSON
{META_DATA}: (confused by this)
{DIALOGUE}: We thought maybe you'd have that kind of information for us.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{META_DATA}: (feigning surprise)
{DIALOGUE}: This is a very different proposition.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Johnson and Hughes exchange a glance.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHNSON
{DIALOGUE}: We pay for that kind of information.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A fat kid in an inner-tube floats behind them.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHNSON
{DIALOGUE}: Is that what you're talking about, Javier?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javi makes eye contact with one agent, then the other.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{DIALOGUE}: Ten years ago Tijuana had no drug problem.
{DIALOGUE}: Now it is epidemic.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Ten years ago America takes a hammer to Pablo Escobar, a hammer to the Miami drug trade, and you allowed everything to move to my country.
{DIALOGUE}: You dumped the problem at our feet.
{DIALOGUE}: Now, drug use is epidemic.
{DIALOGUE}: Now, the treatment centers are full and get no state money.
{DIALOGUE}: They survive on donations and what they get for building doghouses to sell to the U.S.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: We need lights for the parks so kids can play at night.
{DIALOGUE}: So they can play baseball.
{DIALOGUE}: So it's safe.
{DIALOGUE}: Everybody likes parks.
{DIALOGUE}: Everybody likes baseball.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: What I'm talking about is I would like to see somebody take an interest in Tijuana.
{DIALOGUE}: That's what I'm talking about.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javi starts to get out of the pool.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HUGHES
{DIALOGUE}: Javi, You want to come see us again, you're going on the box.
{DIALOGUE}: No more of this water-wing bullshit.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. PARKING GARAGE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javier gets out of the DEA sedan and back into his.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He drives away.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SEDAN - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Agents Hughes turns to Agent Johnson.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHNSON
{DIALOGUE}: You wanna tell me what the hell that was all about?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HUGHES
{DIALOGUE}: He's got something.
{DIALOGUE}: We just have to be patient.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. JAIL VISITATION ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena and Carl each hold a telephone receiver as they stare at each other through a thick pane of meshed glass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena is barely holding it together.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's hard for Carl to see her like this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After a beat --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARL
{DIALOGUE}: How's David?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: How's David?
