{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARL
{DIALOGUE}: Helena --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: Tell me what to do, Carl.
{DIALOGUE}: I need guidance, not a fucking platitude.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm not bringing a child into the kind of life I grew up with.
{DIALOGUE}: I won't do it.
{DIALOGUE}: I want our life back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carl looks at his wife as if he is trying to weigh her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He thinks, then leans forward --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARLOS
{DIALOGUE}: I built our house and I don't want to lose it.
{DIALOGUE}: Every stone, every brick, every board.
{META_DATA}: (carefully)
