{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ROBERT IN HIS CAR
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: I'm looking for my daughter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The dealer looks at him with disgust, turns his back, and waves everyone else away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert slams his fist against the steering wheel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slams it again and again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stops and pulls away, just as
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AT THE INTERSECTION
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: behind Robert's car, Caroline crosses the street toward Sketch's house.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SKETCH'S BEDROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A single candle lights the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caroline is underneath Sketch the drug dealer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is pounding away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As she clutches his back and holds on, her expression is both surprised and druggy, and SOUNDS escape her mouth that she wouldn't believe she could make.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's a KNOCK on the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sketch continues his business.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The KNOCKING is more insistent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finally, he stops and gets up and goes to the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caroline lies back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's in a bed with black sheets in a room with nothing else in it but a dresser and some duffle bags.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sketch opens the door --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SKETCH
{DIALOGUE}: What the fuck do you want?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SOMEBODY outside says something.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sketch walks over to a duffle bag and extracts some product.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caroline's eyes are glued to it as Sketch hands it through the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sketch sees her staring at the drugs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He comes back to bed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SKETCH
{DIALOGUE}: You want some of that?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caroline nods.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SKETCH
{DIALOGUE}: What you gonna do to get some of that?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{DIALOGUE}: Please --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SKETCH
{DIALOGUE}: What you gonna do?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns her back to him, pouting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He laughs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SKETCH
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe a taste.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He reaches over beside the bed where there is a small tray.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the tray is a rig, spoon, several powders, and an eye dropper.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls the candle over and rapidly fixes a speedball.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls the fluid into the neck of the syringe and holds it up the light.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It has Caroline transfixed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SKETCH
{DIALOGUE}: Feed this to you like a little bird.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He squirts the tiniest amount of fluid into the air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It arcs in the candlelight.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{DIALOGUE}: Don't --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SKETCH
{DIALOGUE}: You want this?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She nods.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SKETCH
{DIALOGUE}: This is the Express train.
{DIALOGUE}: Baby turnin' pro and getting down in a big, big hole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her concentration is entirely, hypnotically focused on the syringe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sketch moves the syringe toward her lips.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SKETCH
{DIALOGUE}: Kiss it.
{DIALOGUE}: Kiss your new mommy hello.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caroline moves her mouth toward the side of the syringe, her lips part.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sketch pulls the sheet back, exposing her legs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He grips one powerful hand around her ankle and squeezes... Veins stand out on her foot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slides the needle into the largest vein and slowly depresses the plunger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caroline watches, then her head tilts back, then forward, she GROANS, sexually and slumps against the pillows, her eyes half-open, her lips twitching.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sketch puts the rig back on the tray, then admires Caroline's beauty for a second before starting to fuck her again.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. HOTEL - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon and Castro and two other AGENTS escort Ruiz out of the hotel and usher him into a waiting cruiser.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They pull out in a caravan and move through the streets toward the courthouse.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. COURTHOUSE PARKING LOT - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The cruiser pulls into a fenced and gated parking lot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon, Castro and Ruiz, walking with a limp, cross to the building entrance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As they push inside, Francisco Flores, in a conservative grey suit passes them going outside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The parking lot is empty of people.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The guards at the gate talk about something distracting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Francisco passes by the cruiser and drops his keys.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Kneeling down he extracts a small, powerful, magnetized bomb from his jacket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He attaches it to the underside of the vehicle, stands and walks toward the guard gate.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. COURTROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The court is filled to capacity.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena and Metzger watch from the gallery.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The JUDGE bangs his gavel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Adler is on his feet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ADLER
{DIALOGUE}: Your honor, it has come to our attention that your honor, while in private practice, previously represented the town of Seal Beach in their stop-work suit against the Police Department of Seal Beach.
{DIALOGUE}: We believe this disqualifies you from hearing this case and we therefore move for a temporary suspension while this is investigated.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The judge is surprised to hear this.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JUDGE
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. Adler, this is a most unusual motion.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ADLER
{DIALOGUE}: Nonetheless, your honor, we feel that our client deserves every fairness afforded under the law.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JUDGE
{DIALOGUE}: If this is in any way designed to delay the testimony of Eduardo Ruiz...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The judge considers.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JUDGE
{DIALOGUE}: We'll recess until 9:00 am Monday morning.
{DIALOGUE}: And I'll see counsel in chambers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slams the gavel down again.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. COURTHOUSE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon, Castro, other AGENTS and Ruiz come down the rear steps of the courthouse and walk across the street toward the parking lot.
