{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HELENA'S CAR - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena drives her car through downtown San Diego.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{META_DATA}: (into phone)
{DIALOGUE}: You've got a gun.
{DIALOGUE}: Get out of the car and shoot him in the head.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. FRANCISCO'S CAR - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Francisco watches Ruiz and the agents walk up the street toward him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANCISCO
{META_DATA}: (into phone)
{DIALOGUE}: They're going to walk right past me.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: What are you?
{DIALOGUE}: A mouse?
{DIALOGUE}: Get out of the car and do it.
{DIALOGUE}: This is your chance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Francisco watches the three men walk past his car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He makes a decision and opens his door.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. STREET - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Francisco steps from the car and mingles in with OTHER PEOPLE walking along the sidewalk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He follows them for few yards, picking his moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He closes the distance to Gordon, Castro and Ruiz, pulling a pistol from inside his jacket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He takes careful aim from twelve feet away and is about to shoot Ruiz when a bullet hole appears in his chest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He staggers, trying to squeeze the trigger, Francisco fires the gun once, wildly --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A tourist screams --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon and Castro and Ruiz turn --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Francisco is looking down at the widening red splotch in the center of his shirt, uncertain of what has happened --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon shoves Ruiz down into a doorway and fires three quick shots --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Francisco spins around and drops on his face in the street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Citizens run in all directions fearing a psychopath with an NRA card coming off a bad week of day-trading --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon and Castro with Ruiz beneath them scan the streets.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CASTRO
{DIALOGUE}: Stay here.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll get the car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Castro runs down the street for the court parking lot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Other AGENTS are running toward Gordon and Ruiz.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. OFFICE BUILDING WINDOW - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The STRANGE MAN who threatened Helena's children packs a high-caliber rifle and scope into a briefcase.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He snaps the case shut and quickly exits the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We notice a man on the floor with a bullet hole in his head next to the open door.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. STREET - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Agents surround Ruiz.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon walks to the body of Francisco lying face down in the gutter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns him over with his shoe and sees his face.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GORDON
{META_DATA}: (to the other agents)
{DIALOGUE}: I saw this guy at the courthouse.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: The car --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon takes off running, yelling for Castro.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. COURT PARKING LOT - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Castro has reached the car and gets in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon appears at the gate of the lot --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GORDON
{META_DATA}: (yelling)
{DIALOGUE}: No --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CRUISER - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Castro turns the ignition exactly at the moment he sees Gordon yelling and waving his arms --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. COURT PARKING LOT - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The cruiser EXPLODES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon hits the pavement.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Parts of the car begin raining down around him.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMITTED
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SIDEWALK CAFE - SAN DIEGO - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A fire truck and paramedic unit WHIZZES by.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Manolo sits at an outdoor cafe table, waiting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He can't help looking around at the attractive people, but he's also nervous.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly two MEN, recognizable as Salazar's OFFICERS from the desert drug bust, sitting at a nearby table, rise and move to Manolo's table.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAN #1
{DIALOGUE}: Manolo, how are you?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They take seats uncomfortably close to Manolo.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAN #2
{DIALOGUE}: Manolo, have we interrupted?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: You're looking around like you're expecting someone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MANOLO
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm looking for the waiter.
{DIALOGUE}: I want to order.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAN #1
{DIALOGUE}: What are you gonna have?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MANOLO
{DIALOGUE}: A steak.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAN #1
{DIALOGUE}: Well, if you like steak, we know a much better place.
{DIALOGUE}: We'll take you there.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MANOLO
{DIALOGUE}: That's okay, really.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They each take Manolo by an arm.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAN #2
{DIALOGUE}: Manolo, we should really be going now, before it gets too crowded.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SUV - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We're looking through the windshield as we approach the Mexican border.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the car slows, we pan to follow the border official as he looks in briefly and waves us through.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We continue to pan to reveal Manolo in the backseat sitting beside Man #2.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. SUV - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We're in the desert.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's nothing in any directions.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javi is implacable.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Manolo understands what is happening.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MANOLO
{DIALOGUE}: I was going to feed them wrong information.
{DIALOGUE}: Feed them lies to... it was for...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The men say nothing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After a beat --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MANOLO
{DIALOGUE}: Don't tell Anna I died like this.
{DIALOGUE}: Tell her it was something else.
{DIALOGUE}: Tell her it was official business.
{DIALOGUE}: Tell her that I died doing something honorable.
{DIALOGUE}: Please, tell her that for me...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. DESERT - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javi and Manolo stand next to two freshly dug graves.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAN #1
{DIALOGUE}: Turn around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javi hesitates before turning.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We're on Javi as we hear the GUNSHOT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javi doesn't flinch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Manolo's body falls into the grave.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javi stands there, waiting.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAN #1
{DIALOGUE}: You got anything you want to say?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javi shakes his head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finally, another GUNSHOT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After a beat, a hand reaches out of Javi's shoulder.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAN #1
{DIALOGUE}: Sorry about that... we had to be sure.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They walk back to the SUV.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SOMEBODY ELSE
{DIALOGUE}: Are you sure you don't have anything to tell us?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javi says nothing, doesn't even acknowledge them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear a GUNSHOT.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. AYALA HOME - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arnie Metzger is in Helena's living room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The stereo is loudly playing MOZART.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE
{DIALOGUE}: That was a stupid thing you did.
{DIALOGUE}: Incredibly stupid.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: I tried, Arnie.
{DIALOGUE}: And, I will continue to try.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE
{DIALOGUE}: Have you gone crazy?
{DIALOGUE}: You are not Carl.
{DIALOGUE}: You aren't as good as Carl.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: They are moving the trial to a high security location.
{DIALOGUE}: The press has gone berserk.
{DIALOGUE}: The jury will be influenced.
{DIALOGUE}: Stay out of things.
{DIALOGUE}: Let us try to win the case.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: That is going to be rather difficult when all the evidence is against us.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena steps closer to Arnie, close enough that her breasts are almost touching his chest.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE
{DIALOGUE}: Helena, please.
{DIALOGUE}: This is out of your hands.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{META_DATA}: (softly)
{DIALOGUE}: I know I made things worse.
{DIALOGUE}: I know that and I'm sorry, but Arnie I need something from you.
{DIALOGUE}: Something only you can help me with.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena looks searchingly into his eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE
{DIALOGUE}: Helena --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: I need an introduction to the Obregon Brothers.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE
{DIALOGUE}: I can't do that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena leans closer to him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: I figured out what Carl was up to and I need your help.
{DIALOGUE}: Will you help me?
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. LABORATORY RESEARCH FACILITIES - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An establishing shot of a hi-tech company within shooting distance of the Salk Institute.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. LAB FACILITY - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This is a professional chemical lab that can be rented by the month.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Long tables of lab and computer equipment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nobody has been here in a while.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There are toys - plastic dolls, frisbees, hula hoops - on many of the tables.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena lets herself into the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She scans ledgers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks over the equipment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She picks up a twelve-inch high plastic Spastic Jack action figure and a can labeled "solvent" and hurries from the lab.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. WEST END - CINCINNATI - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert drives through the streets, searching for Caroline.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He doesn't find her.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. WAKEFIELD HOUSE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barbara is waiting in the living room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert enters.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He shakes his head then stands silently for a beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: About the other night, I'm sorry.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARBARA
{DIALOGUE}: Me, too.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: God, I don't get it.
{DIALOGUE}: Are we supposed to say to ourselves, be prepared to lose her, be prepared to lose our child?
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Why does this happen to someone?
{DIALOGUE}: How does it happen?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARBARA
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CAROLINE'S BEDROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert is standing in the middle of her room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's not sure what he's looking for.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Everywhere he looks: her personal things, beloved objects from more innocent times, pictures.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Within moments a legitimate desire to connect with his daughter has escalated into a search for clues.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He opens her drawers, dumps little boxes, pulls things off of shelves.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He becomes increasingly unhinged, flinging things around her room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He tosses a stack of magazines.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A fashion magazine, airborne, discharges some contents: a lighter, a plastic tube and a piece of folded aluminum foil fluttering to the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert stares at the foil on the carpet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's charred on the outside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He picks it up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And unfolds it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's a dried milky white substance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He picks up the tube and lighter and stares at them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then, somewhat tentatively, he puts the tube in his mouth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He holds the lighter under the foil, then heats the milky substance which turns translucent and disappears in a cloud of smoke.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert sucks all of it in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He waits a long time then exhales.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes shut.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The tube drops from his mouth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He staggers and, overwhelmed by the sensations, sits on the bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The lighter and foil fall from his hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A moment later he opens his eyes and doesn't seem to know where he is.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks at the room, confused.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stumbles to the door and shuts it firmly behind him.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MANOLO'S HOUSE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna is weeping.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javier sits next to her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He puts his arm around her and she leans her head against his shoulder.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. JAVIER'S SUV - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javi drives through the streets of Tijuana.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He brakes for a stop sign and watches, trance-like, the pedestrians crossing in front of him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the intersection clears he remains still.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A HONK from behind brings him back and he pulls forward passing Helena Ayala who crosses going the opposite direction.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We stay with her.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. TIJUANA - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena walks down a nightlife street that is tawdry and stale in the midday sun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMITTED
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CLUB PLATINUM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A shrewd Obregon Lieutenant, JUAN MARQUEZ, 40, sits at a table opposite Helena.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Strange Man who both threatened Helena's child and executed Francisco sits in another chair.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: Mrs. Ayala.
{DIALOGUE}: Thank you for coming.
{DIALOGUE}: I am Juan Marquez, I work for Mr. Obregon.
{DIALOGUE}: I believe you know my associate, "Tigrillo," the Little Tiger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena nods to Tigrillo --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: Yes, he threatened to kill my five year-old son.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: I was under the impression I would be meeting Juan Obregon.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: No, this is not possible.
{DIALOGUE}: And I thank you for coming down here, though I suspect it's been a pointless journey.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: Why do you say that, Mr. Marquez?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: I hear these stories.
{DIALOGUE}: Your husband in jail.
{DIALOGUE}: His business in chaos.
{DIALOGUE}: Various people fighting over the scraps.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: My husband is the victim of an informer in your organization, not ours.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: That is not true, Mrs. Ayala.
{DIALOGUE}: Your route is compromised.
{DIALOGUE}: Perhaps it is time for me to deal with other distributors in California.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: I don't think you're going to do that.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: You don't?
{DIALOGUE}: Listen to this woman in a man's world, a very violent world.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: There are plenty of other suppliers in Mexico.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: But not in whose interest it is to help you out of debt.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena reaches into her bag and pulls out the Spastic Jack action figure.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She puts it on the desk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: My husband had been working on something he called, The Project for the Children.
{DIALOGUE}: Are you aware of this?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know.
{DIALOGUE}: Perhaps I remember something.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: We have the ability to change the color, odor, and physical property of cocaine.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: You want to smuggle narcotics in Mr. Espastico Jacobo.
{DIALOGUE}: That's nothing new.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: Not in...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Juan Marquez is confused.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: This doll is cocaine.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Juan picks up Spastic Jack and looks at him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He bangs it on the desk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: Every part, from his ears to his accessory belt, is high-impact, pressure-molded cocaine.
{DIALOGUE}: Odorless.
{DIALOGUE}: Undetectable by dogs.
{DIALOGUE}: Undetectable by anyone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: I don't believe you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She takes out the "solvent" and puts it on his desk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: Get a bowl.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CLUB PLATINUM - OFFICE - LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spastic Jack is slowly dissolving in a bowl of solvent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Only his shoulders, head, and ridiculous ears remain above the quicksand of milky glop.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena holds a mirror under the desk lamp.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is drying the paste.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She puts the mirror on the desk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A white substance has coagulated there.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: Try it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Juan takes out a razor blade and chops the dried substance into two white powder lines.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hands a silver straw to Helena.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: You first.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: I'm six months pregnant.
{DIALOGUE}: I won't do it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: Fine, then we don't have deal.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: Fine, then we don't have a deal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She stands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He watches her a beat, then smiles.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: Okay, okay.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He leans down and quickly snorts a line.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: After a beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: That's good coke.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: It should be... It's yours.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: I want our debt forgiven.
{DIALOGUE}: I want to be the exclusive distributor of Obregon Brothers Cocaine for the United States.
{DIALOGUE}: And I want the principle witness against my husband, Eduardo Ruiz, killed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: Perhaps... Perhaps... I'm afraid I must first ask you to pass a test.
{DIALOGUE}: I asked the same of your husband and he succeeded with flying colors.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena waits.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Juan Marquez reaches in his desk and pulls out a quarter kilo of cocaine.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pushes it across the desk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: Take this back with you.
{DIALOGUE}: Deliver it safely to Tigrillo in San Diego and we have a deal.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: That's crazy.
{DIALOGUE}: My husband is on trial for smuggling.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: Exactly, and this is how I know I'm not getting into business with the U.S. Government.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She puts the quarter key in her bag and stands.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: You will help me with my other problem.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: Deliver that safely to Tigrillo in San Diego.
{DIALOGUE}: And we have a deal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tigrillo escorts her out of the room.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CLUB PLATINUM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena follows Tigrillo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As they pass the restrooms she signals that she has to stop.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CLUB PLATINUM - LADIES' ROOM - DAY
