{DIALOGUE}: Would you like to read it first or shall we proceed?
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. FUNERAL SERVICE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hundreds of DEA AGENTS, spouses, others stand around a grave in a leafy cemetery in working class San Diego.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. CEMETERY - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The funeral is over and people are filing back to the cars.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon walks away from the service when he is approached by a mourning LUCINDA CASTRO, the mother of the deceased.
