{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CLASSROOM - CINCINNATI COUNTRY DAY - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bored children of privilege, wearing their blazers or uniform grey skirts, stare at a TEACHER behind a desk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door opens and Robert enters.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He finds Seth Abrahms in the back of the class and walks straight to him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert grabs a fistful of shirt and tie.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SETH
{DIALOGUE}: Hey man, what are you doing?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TEACHER (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Excuse me?
{DIALOGUE}: Excuse me?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert yanks Seth out of his seat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The teacher is approaching.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: Seth has to be excused.
{DIALOGUE}: He's going on a field trip.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. THE FUN ZONE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena watches David play a video game.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They have finished their lunch, a mess of pizza rinds.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: Come on.
{DIALOGUE}: Time to go.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The CLOWN tries to catch their attention with some mime, but they ignore him.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. THE FUN ZONE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena and David are pushing out the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The man walking the other way past them is Tigrillo from the Tijuana cartel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As they pass --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{META_DATA}: (under her breath)
{DIALOGUE}: Women's room, stall two.
{META_DATA}: (loud)
{DIALOGUE}: Should we stop for ice-cream?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DAVID
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tigrillo disappears into the restaurant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As Helena pulls out of the Fun Zone parking lot, an unmarked DEA cruiser falls in behind her.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ROBERT'S CAR - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert and Seth are parked across the street from Sketch's building.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They watch people, mostly white people, get what they need.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SETH
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know, maybe we missed her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: I can't believe you used to bring my daughter here, to this place.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SETH
{DIALOGUE}: Hey man, back the fuck up.
{DIALOGUE}: To this place.
{DIALOGUE}: What's that shit?
{DIALOGUE}: Right now, all over this country, a hundred thousand white people from the suburbs are driving around downtown asking every black person they see, You got any drugs?
{DIALOGUE}: You know where I can get drugs?
{DIALOGUE}: What kind of effect you think this has on the psyche of a black person, on their possibilities?
{DIALOGUE}: If you sent a hundred thousand black people into your neighborhood, Indian Hills, and they asked every white person they saw, hey, you got any drugs?
{DIALOGUE}: , within a day, your friends and their kids would be selling.
{DIALOGUE}: It's market forces, man.
{DIALOGUE}: The product's marked up three hundred percent.
{DIALOGUE}: You can go out on the street and make five hundred bucks in two hours and then do whatever you want for the rest of the day.
{DIALOGUE}: You think white people would still be going to law school?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's a beat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: You're starting to piss me off.
{DIALOGUE}: Get out of the car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert and Seth get our of the car and walk across the street.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HALLWAY - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert and Seth stand in the dim, dingy hallway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A JUNKIE leaves.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SETH
{DIALOGUE}: You're gonna get me killed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert shoves Seth toward the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Seth knocks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door opens a crack and Sketch's face appears.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SKETCH
{DIALOGUE}: What do you want?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert moves around Seth.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: I'm looking for my daughter, Caroline.
{DIALOGUE}: She comes here.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SKETCH
{DIALOGUE}: This is a business.
{DIALOGUE}: Get the fuck outta here.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: I need to find my daughter.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll pay you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sketch pulls a gun and shoves it against Robert's cheek.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SKETCH
{DIALOGUE}: Who the fuck do you think you are?
{DIALOGUE}: Where the fuck do you think you are?
{DIALOGUE}: Why the fuck do you think I shouldn't just put you in a dumpster?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: I have money --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SKETCH
{DIALOGUE}: I got money.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: I'll pay you a thousand dollars.
{DIALOGUE}: I have it in my wallet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SKETCH
{DIALOGUE}: I want your money, I'll take your money.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: Just tell me where she is.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sketch pushes Robert back into the hall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sketch sees Seth lurking there.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SKETCH
{META_DATA}: (to Seth)
{DIALOGUE}: Don't do that shit again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sketch slams the door in their face.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SETH
{DIALOGUE}: Great.
{DIALOGUE}: What a good idea.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. STREET - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Seth and Robert walk to the car.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SETH
{DIALOGUE}: Man, I'm telling you.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't do this vigilante thing.
{DIALOGUE}: Either the cops find her or she'll call you.
{DIALOGUE}: I promise.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert looks at him, carefully.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. MANOLO'S HOUSE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javier KNOCKS on the front door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is no answer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The shades are drawn.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The house is darkened.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{META_DATA}: (calling out)
{DIALOGUE}: Anna.
{DIALOGUE}: Anna, please.
{DIALOGUE}: Let me in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He KNOCKS again.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{DIALOGUE}: Come on.
{DIALOGUE}: You can't stay locked in your house all day.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finally, the door cracks open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Anna has clearly not been out of the house since the last time we saw her.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. MANOLO'S HOUSE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javier sits opposite Anna.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{DIALOGUE}: I know this is a tragedy, but you have to realize that good has come out of it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks at him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{DIALOGUE}: If Manolo hadn't gone and told them what he did then Salazar and Madrigal would never have been brought to justice.
{DIALOGUE}: He did a great thing for Tijuana.
{DIALOGUE}: He did a great thing for Mexico.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ANNA
{DIALOGUE}: I want to believe you.
{DIALOGUE}: I really do.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{DIALOGUE}: You will believe me, because it's true.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. SKETCH'S APARTMENT - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Seth walks up the steps and into the building.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A beat later he reappears and continues down the street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert emerges from across the street and follows at a guarded distance.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. STREETS - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Seth walks along the seedy neighborhood street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He approaches the Villa Elaine.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns up the steps and disappears inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert follows him.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. VILLA ELAINE HALLWAY - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert ascends the stairs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he enters the hallway he sees Seth pounding on one of the doors.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SETH
{DIALOGUE}: Open the door.
{DIALOGUE}: Open the fucking door, man.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A MAN'S VOICE comes from the other side of the door.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MUFFLED VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: Go away!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert closes the distance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Seth pounds harder.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SETH
{DIALOGUE}: I know she's in there.
{DIALOGUE}: Let me talk to her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MUFFLED VOICE
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know what you're talking about.
{DIALOGUE}: Go away!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert reaches the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Seth sees him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SETH
{DIALOGUE}: I know she's in there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert kicks the door in.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOTEL ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert sees a middle-aged JOHN in his underwear and a dress shirt.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Hey, I haven't touched her --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caroline is passed out on the bed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert goes to her as the John scrambles for his clothes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She stirs and sees him --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{META_DATA}: (really out of it)
{DIALOGUE}: Hi, Daddy.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ROBERT'S CAR - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caroline rides in the passenger seat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's come out of her stupor and is now filled with ebullience.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{DIALOGUE}: It's gonna be great... I mean, I'm okay and all, because, see, I met a guy, he's in this pretty famous band and...
{META_DATA}: (gets up confessional courage)
{DIALOGUE}: They've invited me to write lyrics for them, I'm gonna be able to do that and maybe sing, too... not at first, but later.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caroline gets lost in her grandiose vision.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert looks over at her as she drifts off into a nod.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A moment later she's awake and rambling again.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{META_DATA}: (sounding completely crazy)
{DIALOGUE}: I've been doing research for the school paper, that's what I've been doing, like on assignment kind-of, I've seen some stuff you wouldn't believe, but I'm gonna write it all down into lyrics.
{DIALOGUE}: They think I'm really good, everybody says so, what do you think?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert fights back tears.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He reaches over and takes his daughter's hand.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMITTED
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMITTED
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMITTED
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMITTED
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMITTED
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMITTED
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMITTED
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMITTED
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CLUB PLATINUM OFFICE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Juan Marquez sits across the desk from Javi.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tigrillo and PABLO, 30's, are also in the meeting.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: Salazar and Madrigal are no longer with us.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: A feat none of these people could get accomplished.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Juan nods toward Pablo and Tigrillo.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MARQUEZ
{DIALOGUE}: You're going to be made the Special Assistant to the new drug Czar, which makes you a very valuable law enforcement officer.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: I hope you like to travel because we have plans for Juarez and El Paso, Nogales, Sinaloa, Jalisco, Michoacan...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javi just stares at him for a long moment, then looks off.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ROBERT'S OFFICE IN WASHINGTON - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert on the telephone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{META_DATA}: (into phone)
{DIALOGUE}: How was she?
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BARBARA'S OFFICE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A cramped, messy office at the Environmental Protection Agency.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barbara is on the phone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARBARA
{META_DATA}: (into phone)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm really not sure.
{DIALOGUE}: She seemed to recognize it wasn't Serenity Oaks.
{DIALOGUE}: It's a pretty hard-core facility, but at least we know where she is.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe it's what she needs now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: INTERCUT ROBERT IN HIS OFFICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He holds the phone and doesn't say anything.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. COURTROOM - EARLY MORNING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The court is searched carefully by a phalanx of OFFICERS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Metal Detectors are checked.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bomb sniffing German Shepherds are led through the space.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HOTEL SUITE - MORNING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The agents are unkempt and everyone is tired.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ruiz moves through a cluttered room in a bathrobe with a cup of coffee.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An agent shows him a morning paper --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT
{DIALOGUE}: Big day.
{META_DATA}: (shows picture in paper)
{DIALOGUE}: You're a star.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ruiz walks over and sits across from Gordon, switching off the radio show he's listening to.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon looks up from his paper.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GORDON
{DIALOGUE}: Go shower.
{DIALOGUE}: You smell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is a KNOCK on the front door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An AGENT goes to answer --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: AGENT
{DIALOGUE}: Who is it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SOMEBODY (V.O.)
{META_DATA}: (through the door)
{DIALOGUE}: The Mafia.
{DIALOGUE}: I've got his breakfast.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The agent opens the door and is handed a breakfast tray.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He puts the food in front of Ruiz who uncovers the sausage and eggs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An agent walking by tries to take a bite of sausage.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ruiz stabs it with a fork --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUIZ
{DIALOGUE}: Fuck off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon watches the interchange --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GORDON
{DIALOGUE}: Where's the love gone, Eddie?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: You'll be testifying for at least ten days.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: What if we stop feeding you?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ruiz begins to eat hungrily.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUIZ
{DIALOGUE}: You expect me to be grateful for spending the rest of my life looking over my shoulder.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GORDON
{DIALOGUE}: That thought makes me feel awful.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ruiz pushes eggs into a piece of toast.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUIZ
{DIALOGUE}: Can't you for a second imagine none of this had happened?
{DIALOGUE}: That my drugs had gone through.
{DIALOGUE}: What would have been the harm?
{DIALOGUE}: A few people get high who are getting high anyway.
{DIALOGUE}: Your partner is still alive.
{DIALOGUE}: We avoid having breakfast together.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't you see this means nothing?
{DIALOGUE}: That your whole life is pointless?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GORDON
{DIALOGUE}: You're breaking my heart.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUIZ
{DIALOGUE}: The worst thing about you, Monty, is you realize the futility of what you're doing and you do it anyway.
{DIALOGUE}: I wish you could see how transparent you are.
{META_DATA}: (disgusted)
{DIALOGUE}: This food tastes like shit.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GORDON
{DIALOGUE}: So go shower already.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RUIZ
{DIALOGUE}: You only got to me because you were tipped off by the Juarez Cartel, who's trying to break into Tijuana.
{DIALOGUE}: You're helping them.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: You work for a drug dealer too, Monty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ruiz stands and heads for the bathroom.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GORDON
{META_DATA}: (yelling after him)
{DIALOGUE}: And shave.
{DIALOGUE}: You better look nice and believable for the jury.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ruiz disappears into the bathroom and slams the door behind him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GORDON
{META_DATA}: (to another agent)
{DIALOGUE}: It's like having another wife.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The agent laughs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's another KNOCK on the door.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GORDON
{DIALOGUE}: Who is it?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SOMEBODY ELSE (V.O.)
{META_DATA}: (though the door)
{DIALOGUE}: Breakfast.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon and the agent look at each other.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SOMEBODY ELSE
{DIALOGUE}: Hurry up.
{DIALOGUE}: It's getting cold.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon moves to the side of the door and pulls his gun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The other agent opens the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A MAN with a breakfast tray enters.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon puts the gun to the side of his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAN WITH TRAY
{DIALOGUE}: I'm on your side.
{DIALOGUE}: God, you're jumpy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon is momentarily confused, then goes for the bathroom door.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GORDON
{DIALOGUE}: Call an ambulance.
{DIALOGUE}: Hurry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon tries the bathroom door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's stuck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gets it open a crack.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's a body against the other side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He shoves.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. BATHROOM - CONTINUOUS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ruiz is on the floor in convulsions.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GORDON
{META_DATA}: (yelling)
{DIALOGUE}: Call the ambulance.
{META_DATA}: (to Ruiz)
{DIALOGUE}: Don't die on me.
{DIALOGUE}: You will not die on me.
{DIALOGUE}: Do you hear me?
{DIALOGUE}: Don't you die on me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ruiz's convulsions get worse, his claw-like fingers scratch across the tile.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMITTED
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. COURTROOM - SAN DIEGO - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The court is packed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena and Arnie watch from the gallery.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The judge is at the bench.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The prosecutor rises --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PROSECUTOR
{DIALOGUE}: Your honor, ladies and gentlemen of the jury... Because of the sudden death of Eduardo Ruiz, the people have decided that at this point we cannot continue our case against Carl Ayala.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The court ERUPTS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reporters scatter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena cheers.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMITTED
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. WHITE HOUSE OFFICE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert Wakefield enters the office of the Chief of Staff, who looks up from what he's doing, which is reading Robert's report, and is already mid-sentence.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHIEF OF STAFF
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, hi --
{META_DATA}: (waves Robert to a chair)
{DIALOGUE}: So I've got a copy of your speech here...
{META_DATA}: (glances down, still reading)
{DIALOGUE}: It's fantastic... So, Robert, my genuine thanks.
{DIALOGUE}: You're my choice and you're gonna be great.
{DIALOGUE}: The President is sorry he hasn't been able to spend more time with you.
{DIALOGUE}: After the press conference he wants to really sit down.
{META_DATA}: (an afterthought)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, I got to the Post, too.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't worry about that thing with your daughter, it's not news; they're willing to treat it as a family matter, a personal matter.
{META_DATA}: (off Robert's stare)
{DIALOGUE}: Look, even if it came out, we'd turn it into a qualification, I've been in the trenches of this Drug War, I have seen the face of the enemy, etcetera.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert just stares at him.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. JAIL CELL - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: General Salazar sits in the same grimy cell that housed Francisco Flores.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is sweating and his breathing is labored.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A DOCTOR enters and gives him an injection, explaining that it will calm him down.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. DESERT OUTSIDE TIJUANA - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's a reprise of the earlier desert bust... a landing strip in the middle of nowhere, a plane landing, SUV's approaching.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This time Javi is at the wheel of one of them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: News crews are trailing behind him.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. DESERT AIRSTRIP - LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javi and Special Agent Hughes stand next to a giant mound of seized cocaine, the same cocaine, in fact, Javi held briefly at the beginning.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The same teenagers from the pickup truck have been arrested.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The news crews get everything.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{META_DATA}: (to the press)
{DIALOGUE}: This seizure is one of the largest seizures in Mexican history... It represents the first bilateral effort of the American DEA and the Mexican I.N.C.D.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. JAIL CELL - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: General Salazar lies on his side, eyes and mouth open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is dead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javier looks at him through the doorway.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER (V.O. CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Today I'm very proud to announce that Mexico, with the help of our American partners, is finally winning the war against narcotics trafficking.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The PRESS begins shouting questions --
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMITTED
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HEADQUARTERS, I.N.C.D. - MEXICO - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert and Javi walk through the headquarters, a nondescript government building.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert extracts photographs of the bust from a manila envelope.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The crates of cocaine are clearly marked "911."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: The cocaine brand, 911, is an East Coast brand, a Juarez Cartel brand, and you must know it usually comes through into El Paso?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{DIALOGUE}: I'm aware of that.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: So what's it doing in Tijuana?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javi looks Robert Wakefield squarely in the eye.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He shrugs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: Let me ask you a hypothetical question: if Salazar worked for Madrigal and the Juaraz cartel, and he went out of power, would it mean the Juarez Cartel is losing influence?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{DIALOGUE}: It could mean that, yes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: That would probably mean the Tijuana Cartel is gaining power?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{DIALOGUE}: It's possible.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: Is it possible to have a Drug Czar in Mexico who isn't connected in some war to one of the cartels?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javi thinks along time before answering.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JAVIER
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, it's possible... if you're prepared to die.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. AYALA FRONT YARD - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An outdoor party is going on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Children and adults arrive and mingle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caterers work the barbecue grill.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Waiters serve food and drink on the rolling lawn.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena circles through the crowd greeting friends.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks past her tree line and up the street where a telephone repair van is parked.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns back toward her guests.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Somebody has raised a cup and everyone is CHEERING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena drinks with her guests, then walks inside her house.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AT THE FRONT GATE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Montel Gordon walks through the gate and up the drive.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He grabs a drink off the tray of a passing waiter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He appears drunk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Montel follows Helena into the house.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CARL'S PRIVATE STUDY - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carl hears the CHEERING outside and the sound of LAUGHTER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He makes a cellular telephone call.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ARNIE METZGER'S OFFICE - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arnie is in his office and answers the cell phone --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARLOS (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: It's Saturday, Arnie.
{DIALOGUE}: You work too hard.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE
{DIALOGUE}: Carl, I'm running late.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm coming right now --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind Arnie in the office there is a movement of SHADOW.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CARL'S PRIVATE STUDY - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carl stands at the window looking at his guests while he talks on the phone --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARLOS
{DIALOGUE}: Don't bother.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: What?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARLOS
{DIALOGUE}: So Arnie, when were you going to tell me about the 3 million dollars we got in from San Francisco two days after I got arrested?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: I was just waiting for the right time.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARLOS
{DIALOGUE}: And you didn't feel like you could trust my wife with this news?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: I just didn't want to take a chance.
{DIALOGUE}: I didn't want to risk it.
{DIALOGUE}: It could have been frozen along with everything else.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARLOS
{DIALOGUE}: You had it all figured out.
{DIALOGUE}: You move into my house.
{DIALOGUE}: You raise my kids.
{DIALOGUE}: You sleep with my wife.
{DIALOGUE}: It was a good plan, Arnie.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Carl, that's insane.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARLOS
{DIALOGUE}: So my wife is lying?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Carl, think about it, if I was trying to rip you off, I would have left town after Ruiz was killed.
{DIALOGUE}: I wouldn't sit next to you in court listening to the dismissal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the front lawn CHILDREN are lined up for the ice-cream sundae bar that is being tended by a WAITER.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARLOS
{DIALOGUE}: Arnie, do think there's a difference between a reason and an excuse, because I don't think there is.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ARNIE (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Carl --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARLOS
{DIALOGUE}: Goodbye Arnie.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. ARNIE METZGER'S OFFICE - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Arnie turns around and there are TWO MEN in his office.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CARL'S PRIVATE STUDY - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carl hears MUFFLED GUNSHOTS over the phone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hangs up and turns from the window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena is standing there.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: Who was that?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARLOS
{DIALOGUE}: Arnie.
{DIALOGUE}: He's not going to be able to make the barbecue.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carl and Helena share an embrace and a kiss.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{DIALOGUE}: Come downstairs.
{DIALOGUE}: Everyone is waiting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Carl and Helena turn to leave the room and Montel Gordon is standing in the doorway with his glass of champagne.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GORDON
{DIALOGUE}: Hello, Helena.
{DIALOGUE}: What a great party.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARLOS
{DIALOGUE}: Who are you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GORDON
{DIALOGUE}: Nobody.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm a nobody who arrested you, but your wife is a murderer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon takes a sip of his drink.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two SECURITY OFFICERS appear in the doorway behind him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SECURITY OFFICER
{DIALOGUE}: Hey, you can't be in here.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GORDON
{DIALOGUE}: I'm a cop.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SECURITY OFFICER
{DIALOGUE}: I don't care.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELENA
{META_DATA}: (to the guards)
{DIALOGUE}: Throw him out of here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The security officers grab Gordon.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is a scuffle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon falls to the floor by the window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are wrestling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As they wrestle, Gordon reaches out and, unnoticed, affixes TINY LISTENING DEVICE underneath the desk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He continues to struggle with the guards.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Helena and Carlos start from the room.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GORDON
{META_DATA}: (calling out)
{DIALOGUE}: You didn't win, Helena.
{DIALOGUE}: You lost everything.
{DIALOGUE}: Tell your children a nice bedtime story... How you killed my partner.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. AYALA FRONT YARD - AFTERNOON
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The guests watch as the guards eject Gordon from the premises.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Near the gate David has stopped playing to watch the action.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then he goes back to playing with his toy: a Spastic Jack figure.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VERDANT NEIGHBORHOOD - MEXICO CITY - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javi and his convoy of armored SUV's pull up in front of the beautiful house where earlier he deposited Rosario, Salazar's former mistress.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Javier opens the front door and Rosario greets him by throwing her arms around his neck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They disappear inside.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. WHITE HOUSE PRESS ROOM - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The PRESS SECRETARY stands at the familiar podium addressing the White House Press Corps.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert Wakefield stands to one side with Chief of Staff, his lawyers, Sheridan and General Landry.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: PRESS SECRETARY
{DIALOGUE}: ...a sterling reputation and close friend of the President, recently confirmed into The Office of National Drug Control Policy... our new Drug Czar, Robert Hudson Wakefield.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Applause from the assembled PRESS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Press Secretary signals and Robert walks to the podium.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks back to the Chief of Staff; he stares out at the expectant faces and television lights and camera flashes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{META_DATA}: (reading his prepared speech)
{DIALOGUE}: The War on Drugs is a war on our nation's most precious resource... our children.
{DIALOGUE}: Sixty-eight million children have been targeted by those who perpetrate this war and protecting those children must be priority number one.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: There has been progress and there have been failures, but where we have fallen short I see not a problem but an opportunity.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert is becoming increasingly uneasy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He glances at the Chief of Staff who bores into him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks again at his speech.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With great effort he continues.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: An opportunity to correct the mistakes of the past while laying a solid foundation for the future.
{META_DATA}: (a long, uncomfortable beat)
{DIALOGUE}: This takes not only new ideas, but perseverance.
{DIALOGUE}: This takes not only resources, but courage.
{DIALOGUE}: This takes not only government, but families.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert stops again as though the words are choking him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: I've... I've outlined a ten-point plan, representing a new bilateral effort...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He can't finish.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Everyone stares at Robert.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The crowd of reporters senses something is wrong.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: I can't do this.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: If there is a War on Drugs then our own families have become the enemy.
{DIALOGUE}: How can you wage war on your own family?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He walks out of the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The crowd waits, expecting him to return.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Robert walks down a corridor and out of the White House.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. WHITE HOUSE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A beautiful spring morning.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He walks down to Pennsylvania Avenue.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hails a cab and gets in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The cab pulls away.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. CHURCH BASEMENT - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A twelve step meeting is in progress.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caroline shares from her seat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAROLINE
{DIALOGUE}: On the good days I feel like I get it, like it all makes sense.
{DIALOGUE}: I can stay in the moment.
{DIALOGUE}: I don't have to control everything in the future.
{DIALOGUE}: And I believe everything is going to work out fine.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: On the bad days, I just want to grab the phone and start dialing numbers.
{DIALOGUE}: I want to pull my hair and run through the streets screaming.
{META_DATA}: (beat)
{DIALOGUE}: But, thanks to the people I've met in these rooms, people like Margaret and Jim and Sarah, people who've taught me how to listen, I'm pretty sure I'll make it through today.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Caroline is finished sharing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VOICE (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Would you like to share?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We pan over to reveal Robert and Barbara sitting next to Caroline.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ROBERT
{DIALOGUE}: My name is Robert.
{DIALOGUE}: This is my wife, Barbara.
{DIALOGUE}: We're Caroline's parents.
{DIALOGUE}: We're just hear to listen.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OMIT.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. AYALA HOME - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The house is dark and silent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The van is parked up the street.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. VAN - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gordon listens through a headset, his expression set.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CARLOS (V.O.)
{META_DATA}: (over a listening device)
{DIALOGUE}: We're back up and running.
{DIALOGUE}: Completely untouchable.
{DIALOGUE}: Completely.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BASEBALL FIELD - TIJUANA - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A bank of lights CRANKS on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then ANOTHER and ANOTHER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In a wider shot we see an illuminated baseball field where a children's pickup game is in progress.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the crowd, Javi serenely watches the game.
{META_DATA}: THE END
